<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-07T07:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-07T07:41:00-05:00" n="617" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.001W64/93: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-07T13:00:00+00:19"><hi rend="italic">December 7,
                                        1919, 1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    5.07 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7047. The Minister for Foreign Affairs confided to me the demand for the
                            “extradition” of the ex-Kaiser was about to be made and he asked me if I
                            also knew this and I replied that I did not.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>